# NISHA — Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## 1. Product Overview

**Product Name:** NISHA (Neural Intelligent Surveillance & Hazard Analysis)
**Category:** AI-powered distributed surveillance & behavioral intelligence system

**Description:**
NISHA is a multi-agent, edge-to-cloud AI system designed to detect and classify **violence, suspicious behavior, and abnormal activity in real time** using **computer vision, audio intelligence, and spatial localization**.

The system combines:

* Camera-based perception
* Audio-based detection
* Multi-agent mesh networking
* Real-time analytics and alerting

---

## 2. Objectives

### Primary Goals

* Detect **violence and suspicious behavior in real time**
* Provide **low-latency alerts (<3 seconds)**
* Enable **scalable deployment using distributed agents**
* Operate in **low-infrastructure environments**

### Secondary Goals

* Provide spatial awareness (location estimation)
* Enable historical analytics and trend detection
* Support multi-modal intelligence (vision + audio)

---

## 3. Target Use Cases

* Public security monitoring (streets, campuses)
* Private estate surveillance
* Transport hubs (bus parks, terminals)
* Event crowd monitoring
* Smart city infrastructure

---

## 4. System Architecture

### 4.1 High-Level Flow

```text
Agents → Master Node → Backend Server → AI Engine → Alerts + Dashboard
```

---

### 4.2 Components

#### A. Edge Layer (Agents)

* Hardware: ESP32-CAM / Camera-enabled nodes
* Responsibilities:

  * Capture video/audio
  * Detect motion (PIR/ultrasonic)
  * Stream data to Master
  * Participate in mesh routing

---

#### B. Master Node (Raspberry Pi)

* Aggregates up to 50 agents
* Handles:

  * Local coordination
  * Time synchronization
  * Data buffering
  * Compression and forwarding

---

#### C. Backend Server

* API + orchestration layer
* Handles:

  * Agent lifecycle management
  * Data ingestion
  * Event processing
  * Communication with AI modules

---

#### D. AI Engine

**1. Vision Pipeline**

* Model: YOLOv8 (pose-enabled)
* Output:

  * Person detection
  * Keypoints extraction

**2. Behavior Model**

* Model: LSTM / GRU
* Input:

  * Keypoint sequences (20–30 frames)
* Output:

  * Behavior classification

**Classes:**

* Normal
* Violence
* Suspicious behavior
* Panic/abnormal movement

---

**3. Audio Pipeline**

* Model: YAMNet
* Detects:

  * Gunshots
  * Screams
  * Explosions
  * Distress sounds

---

**4. Fusion Engine**
Combines:

* Vision results
* Audio results
* Context

Outputs:

* Threat score
* Confidence level

---

#### E. Localization Engine (Optional Phase 2)

* Uses multi-agent signal data (RSSI)
* Performs trilateration
* Outputs approximate location

---

#### F. Frontend Dashboard

* Real-time map view
* Live camera feeds
* Alerts panel
* Agent health monitoring
* Event timeline

---

## 5. Functional Requirements

### 5.1 Detection

* Detect humans in real time
* Extract pose keypoints
* Classify behavior within 2–3 seconds

---

### 5.2 Audio Detection

* Process audio in 1–3 second windows
* Detect predefined sound classes

---

### 5.3 Alerts

* Trigger alerts when:

  * High confidence violence detected
  * Audio + vision signals align
* Channels:

  * Dashboard
  * Telegram/SMS

---

### 5.4 Agent Management

* Agent registration and provisioning
* Heartbeat monitoring (30s interval)
* Status tracking:

  * Active
  * Offline
  * Degraded
  * Tampered

---

### 5.5 Mesh Networking

* Multi-hop communication
* Automatic routing
* Failover handling

---

### 5.6 Data Storage

* Store:

  * Event logs
  * Detection metadata
  * Agent state
* Optional:

  * Short video clips (event-based)

---

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance

* Latency: <3 seconds detection-to-alert
* Throughput: Support 100+ agents

### Scalability

* Modular services (AI separated from API)
* Horizontal scaling (multiple AI workers)

### Reliability

* Offline buffering (Master nodes)
* Automatic failover

### Security

* Secure agent authentication
* Encrypted communication

---

## 7. Machine Learning Requirements

### 7.1 Dataset

* Source: Kaggle + custom data
* Classes balanced
* Includes:

  * Real-world noise
  * Crowded environments

---

### 7.2 Training Pipeline

```text
Video → Frames → YOLO Pose → Keypoints → Sequence → LSTM
```

---

### 7.3 Model Specs

| Component | Model             |
| --------- | ----------------- |
| Detection | YOLOv8s / YOLOv8m |
| Behavior  | LSTM / GRU        |
| Audio     | YAMNet            |

---

### 7.4 Metrics

* Accuracy
* Precision / Recall
* F1-score
* Latency

---

## 8. MVP Scope (Phase 1)

### Included:

* Camera input
* YOLOv8 detection
* Pose-based LSTM classification
* Basic alerts (Telegram)
* Simple dashboard

---

### Excluded:

* Full triangulation
* Advanced analytics
* Facial recognition

---

## 9. Phase Roadmap

### Phase 1 (MVP)

* Vision-based detection
* Alerting system

### Phase 2

* Audio integration
* Localization (triangulation)
* Improved UI

### Phase 3

* Multi-camera tracking
* Predictive analytics
* Enterprise features

---

## 10. Risks & Mitigation

| Risk               | Mitigation              |
| ------------------ | ----------------------- |
| False positives    | Fusion (audio + vision) |
| Poor lighting      | Data augmentation       |
| Network failure    | Local buffering         |
| Noisy environments | Audio filtering         |

---

## 11. Success Criteria

* ≥85% accuracy on violence detection
* <3s alert latency
* Stable operation with 50+ agents
* Low false positive rate (<10%)

---

## 12. Future Enhancements

* Transformer-based behavior models
* Edge AI deployment
* Federated learning
* Smart city integrations

---

## 13. Summary

NISHA is a **multi-modal intelligent surveillance platform** combining:

* Computer vision
* Audio intelligence
* Distributed IoT agents
* Real-time analytics

It is designed to be:

* Scalable
* Real-time
* Context-aware
* Adaptable to real-world environments

